article.headline: Norfolk State 77, Hampton 70
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Ryan Grier scored 19 points, 13 in the second half on Saturday as Norfolk St. overcame a six-point second half deficit to defeat Hampton 77-70. After trailing by five, Grier hit a 3-pointer to cap an 11-3 run with 3:39 remaining to give the Spartans (11-16) a 66-63 lead. The Pirates (13-16) came within two points twice, the second time Jared Woodley made a 3-pointer with 2:18 remaining to make it 69-67, but Hampton made 6 of 8 free throws in the final minute to seal the game. Devin Green's dunk with 18:36 left gave Hampton its biggest lead of the game, 44-38, before the Spartans used a 13-2 spurt to take a 51-46 lead. Green finished with 18 points to lead the Pirates. Chakowby Hicks had 18 points and 10 rebounds for the Spartans, who trailed 40-36 at the half. Nicholas Byrd and Tynell Dunkley added 10 points each. Bruce Brown had 15 points and nine rebounds and Jeff Granger had 10 points for the Spartans.
